The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Monday, January 05, 2004 				 Store guard gunned down
 A STAFF REPORTER																								Calcutta, Jan. 4: The security guard of a cellphone outlet in BBD Bag was shot dead this morning. 																								The man, who was later identified as Dilip Mondal, was found lying in a pool of blood inside the outlet with a bullet hole in his neck. The Hutch outlet in Stephen House is a stones throw from Writers Buildings and the police headquarters at Lalbazar. 																								The man (Mondal) was shot after 6.30 am. He was on the morning shift, said an official of Hare Street police station.																								Mondal, 35, was from Malda, and took over charge of the outlet from Rajinder Rai around 6 am. He had joined the security agency as a gunman two years ago and had been posted at the outlet since, said an official.																								Rai, who was about to go home, told Mondal that he had a visitor outside, said an officer. Mondal asked Rai to send him in. On stepping out of the shop half-an-hour later, the man told Rai, who was waiting outside, he would go to Rajabazar. Rai was to go to Howrah. 																								A guard who came to join duty around 9.30 am saw Mondal dead. The shutter was half-closed and Mondal was not in uniform, said Aswini Kumar Pandey.
